	</pre>
	<h3>Definindo as mascaras no HTML.</h3>
	<p>Você pode criar máscaras para os seus campos editando o atributo <code>data-mask</code>, veja o exemplo abaixo:</p>
	<div class="example">
		<form role="form">
			<fieldset>
				<div class="row">
					<div class="form-group col-lg-4">
						<label for="example-input-10">Data</label>
						<input type="text" class="form-control" id="example-input-10" placeholder="Ex.: dd/mm/aaaa" data-mask="00/00/0000">
					</div>
				</div>
			</fieldset>
		</form>
	</div>
	<pre class="lang-html prettyprint linenums">&lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; class=&quot;form-control&quot; placeholder=&quot;Ex.: dd/mm/aaaa&quot; data-mask=&quot;00/00/0000&quot;&gt;</pre>
</article>